what's the best way to unstick a book see i have a paperback textbook that got soaked and the pages dried together so without destroying it in the process how do i get the pages apart the best method to unstick the pages without damaging them which pulling will do is to use a steam iron use the lowest setting for steam and just run the iron over the pages when you are done the book should be stood on end so that the pages can re dry just start at the beginning iron each page the subsequent page will break loose usually after one try as for my source i made paper for hammermill paper company for years Paper Book Bookbinding Wood pulp Textile manufacturing Hemp Sulfuric acid Locomotive USS Uhlmann (DD-687) Inkjet printer Tofu Geothermal power Dry cleaning Plaster Industrial Revolution USS Abbot (DD-629) Coffee Hydrogen Idli Jute Printing press Wagonway British Locomotive and Multiple Unit Numbering and Classification Flax Tea USS Allen M. Sumner (DD-692) Common bean Steam engine Sailing 2005 Atlantic hurricane season Adhesive Energy development Poker jargon Rice Battle of Hampton Roads Flood geology USS William D. Porter (DD-579) BC Rail William Murdoch Diving Vulcanization Publishing Dairy USS Twining (DD-540) Waste management Hay USS Trigger (SS-237) PaX Casting USS Wickes (DD-578) Sand casting Edwards Air Force Base Sugar Sake Stirling engine Cantonese cuisine Tobacco The Diary of a Young Girl Pottery Brewery USS Thresher (SS-200) Drawing Typewriter Computer printer Glossary of firefighting terms Fight Club Open access Virginian Railway Royal Navy Coal Lightning Page replacement algorithms John Bull (locomotive) One-time pad USS Vestal (AR-4) USS Zane (DD-337) USS Talbot (DD-114) Canadian Pacific Railway Harp Tanning Wok Non-standard analysis PHP Sailor Moon Toilet paper Cracking (chemistry) Drill bit Fuel cell Steamboy Electrical wiring Hydrogen economy Eigenvalue, eigenvector and eigenspace Manicure Electric motor Ebook Glass Money The Foundation Series Hydrochlo